Pre-Game Insights: Maarten Paes has joined the Indonesian national team in Bahrain but is not certain to play against Bahrain on October 10, 2024.
Paes arrived last among the Indonesian squad members, who have been in Bahrain since October 6, 2024.
The medical team examined Paes upon arrival due to a wrist injury he sustained while with FC Dallas.
Paes's injury has shown positive progress, and he has been seen training without protective gloves.
Coach Shin Tae-yong stated that Paes has a 70% chance of playing, with a final decision to be made based on his recovery progress.
If Paes cannot play, Ernando Ari Sutaryadi and Nadeo Argawinata are ready to step in as goalkeepers.
The Indonesian defense is expected to be stronger with the presence of Mees Hilgers.
